<a name="Test Statistics">
<h4>
2.7.4.1. Viewing and Exporting Test Statistics
</h4>
</a>
<p>
The user selects <tt>Statistics</tt> in the <tt>Menu</tt> tab and the <tt>Test</tt> tab, the system
displays the dialog shown in Figure 2.7.4.1.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Figure Test Statistic dialog">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/TestStatBlank.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2.7.4.1:  Test Statistic dialog.  </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>
<p>
The top half of the dialog is initially an empty rectangluar box.</br>
The <tt>Select from Test Bank</tt> button opens up the Test Bank dialog. </br>
The user clicks the <tt>Select from Test Bank</tt> and the Graded Test Bank dialog opens in front of the Test Statistic screen.
<br>
<hr>
<a name="The Graded Test Bank dialog">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/CompletedTestBank.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2.7.4.2:  Graded Test Bank dialog.  </p>
<hr>

</br>
   <p>
      The Test Bank dialog opens and only field that is set is the <tt>Status</tt> which is set to "Completed". Only one test's statistics can be viewed at a time. The user choses one test by checking the box and the rest of the checkboxes will gray out indicating only one test can be chosen.  
      When the user has chosen the correct test the user clicks the <tt>Select</tt> button. This transitions back to the Test Statistics dialog.
   </p>
</br>
<hr>
<a name="Filled Test Statistic dialog">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/TestStatPopulated.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2.7.4.3:  Test Statistic dialog with chart.  </p>
</br>
   <p>
      The chart is populated with the data from the selected test. The chart shows the distribution of scores for the chosen test. The x axis represents the possible scores in terms of percentage and is broken into intervals of 20. The y axis represents the number of students. The user views the chart and can see how all of his or her students performed on the exam. 
   </br>
    </br>
      To the right of the chart contains information about the chosen exam.
      <ul>
         <li><tt>Name</tt> - The name of the test.</li>
         <li><tt>Course</tt> - The name of the course in which the test was given.</li>
         <li><tt>Subject</tt> - The subject that the course belongs to.</li>
         <li><tt>Number of Questions</tt> - The number of questions on the test.</li>    
         <li><tt>Difficulty</tt> - The level of difficulty that is decided by the user.</li>
         <li><tt>Date Taken</tt> - The date when the test was given.</li>
         <li><tt>Status</tt> - The graded status of the test.</li>

      </ul>

      The <tt>Export Chart</tt> button takes the all of the data in the rectangular area (the chart and information about the test) and generates a pdf. Then opens the pdf in Adobe Acrobat Reader. 
   </p>
</br>

